        "parents": [
          {
            "commit": "9e3436c298d65a5867920b0de0d3920972465407",
            "subject": "LU-4554 lfsck: old single-OI MDT always scrubbed"
          }
        ],
        "author": {
          "name": "Fan Yong",
          "email": "fan.yong@intel.com",
          "date": "2014-01-31 17:54:40.000000000",
          "tz": 480
        },
        "committer": {
          "name": "Fan Yong",
          "email": "fan.yong@intel.com",
          "date": "2014-01-31 17:54:40.000000000",
          "tz": 480
        },
        "subject": "LU-4445 obdclass: operate lu_device_type fileds properly",
        "message": "LU-4445 obdclass: operate lu_device_type fileds properly\n\nThere was no protection when inc/dec lu_device_type::ldt_device_nr,\nwhich may caused the ldt_device_nr to be wrong and trigger assert.\nThis patch redefine lu_device_type::ldt_device_nr as atomic type.\n\nThere was no protection when add/del lu_device_type::ldt_linkage\ninto/from the global lu_device_types list, which may caused bad\naddress accessing. This patch uses the existing obd_types_lock\nto protect related operations.\n\nWe do NOT need lu_types_stop() any longer. Such function scans\nthe global lu_device_types list, and for each type item on it\nwhich has zerod lu_device_type::ldt_device_nr, call its stop()\nmethod. In fact, the lu_device_type::ldt_device_nr only will be\nzero when the last lu_device_fini() is called, and at that time,\ninside the lu_device_fini(), its stop() method will be called.\nSo it is unnecessary to call the stop() again via lu_types_stop().\n\nSigned-off-by: Fan Yong <fan.yong@intel.com>\nChange-Id: Ia8953ae56e7135414d696c590f7cdd6c8ca9b96e\n"
      },
